verses.text_plain: And the children of Israel set forward, and pitched in the plains of Moab on this side Jordan by Jericho.
verses.verse_html: 1And the children of Israel set forward, and pitched in the plains of Moab on this side Jordan by Jericho.

verses.text_plain: And Balak the son of Zippor saw all that Israel had done to the Amorites.
verses.verse_html: 2And Balak the son of Zippor saw all that Israel had done to the Amorites.

verses.text_plain: And Moab was sore afraid of the people, because they were many: and Moab was distressed because of the children of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 3And Moab was sore afraid of the people, because they were many: and Moab was distressed because of the children of Israel.

verses.text_plain: And Moab said unto the elders of Midian, Now shall this company lick up all that are round about us, as the ox licketh up the grass of the field. And Balak the son of Zippor was king of the Moabites at that time.
verses.verse_html: 4And Moab said unto the elders of Midian, Now shall this company lick up all that are round about us, as the ox licketh up the grass of the field. And Balak the son of Zippor was king of the Moabites at that time.

verses.text_plain: He sent messengers therefore unto Balaam the son of Beor to Pethor, which is by the river of the land of the children of his people, to call him, saying, Behold, there is a people come out from Egypt: behold, they cover the face of the earth, and they abide over against me:
verses.verse_html:
5He sent messengers therefore unto Balaam the son of Beor to Pethor, which is by the river of the land of the children of his people, to call him, saying, Behold, there is a people come out from Egypt: behold, they cover the face of the earth, and they abide over against me: ▼
▼ face: Heb. eye

verses.text_plain: Come now therefore, I pray thee, curse me this people; for they are too mighty for me: peradventure I shall prevail, that we may smite them, and that I may drive them out of the land: for I wot that he whom thou blessest is blessed, and he whom thou cursest is cursed.
verses.verse_html: 6Come now therefore, I pray thee, curse me this people; for they are too mighty for me: peradventure I shall prevail, that we may smite them, and that I may drive them out of the land: for I wot that he whom thou blessest is blessed, and he whom thou cursest is cursed.

tokens.text: now therefore, I pray thee, curse
for me: peradventure I shall prevail

verses.text_plain: And the elders of Moab and the elders of Midian departed with the rewards of divination in their hand; and they came unto Balaam, and spake unto him the words of Balak.
verses.verse_html: 7And the elders of Moab and the elders of Midian departed with the rewards of divination in their hand; and they came unto Balaam, and spake unto him the words of Balak.

verses.text_plain: And he said unto them, Lodge here this night, and I will bring you word again, as the Lord shall speak unto me: and the princes of Moab abode with Balaam.
verses.verse_html: 8And he said unto them, Lodge here this night, and I will bring you word again, as the Lord shall speak unto me: and the princes of Moab abode with Balaam.

verses.text_plain: And God came unto Balaam, and said, What men are these with thee?
verses.verse_html: 9And God came unto Balaam, and said, What men are these with thee?

verses.text_plain: And Balaam said unto God, Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab, hath sent unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 10And Balaam said unto God, Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab, hath sent unto me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Behold, there is a people come out of Egypt, which covereth the face of the earth: come now, curse me them; peradventure I shall be able to overcome them, and drive them out.
verses.verse_html:
11Behold, there is a people come out of Egypt, which covereth the face of the earth: come now, curse me them; peradventure I shall be able to overcome them, and drive them out. ▼
▼ I shall…: Heb. I shall prevail in fighting against him

tokens.text: me them; peradventure I shall be able

footnotes.body_text: ▼ I shall…: Heb. I shall prevail in fighting against him
footnotes.body_html: ▼ I shall…: Heb. I shall prevail in fighting against him

verses.text_plain: And God said unto Balaam, Thou shalt not go with them; thou shalt not curse the people: for they are blessed.
verses.verse_html: 12And God said unto Balaam, Thou shalt not go with them; thou shalt not curse the people: for they are blessed.

tokens.text: with them; thou shalt not curse

verses.text_plain: And Balaam rose up in the morning, and said unto the princes of Balak, Get you into your land: for the Lord refuseth to give me leave to go with you.
verses.verse_html: 13And Balaam rose up in the morning, and said unto the princes of Balak, Get you into your land: for the Lord refuseth to give me leave to go with you.

verses.text_plain: And the princes of Moab rose up, and they went unto Balak, and said, Balaam refuseth to come with us.
verses.verse_html: 14And the princes of Moab rose up, and they went unto Balak, and said, Balaam refuseth to come with us.

verses.text_plain: And Balak sent yet again princes, more, and more honourable than they.
verses.verse_html: 15And Balak sent yet again princes, more, and more honourable than they.

verses.text_plain: And they came to Balaam, and said to him, Thus saith Balak the son of Zippor, Let nothing, I pray thee, hinder thee from coming unto me:
verses.verse_html:
16And they came to Balaam, and said to him, Thus saith Balak the son of Zippor, Let nothing, I pray thee, hinder thee from coming unto me: ▼
▼ Let…: Heb. Be not thou hindered from, etc

tokens.text: Let nothing, I pray thee, hinder

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Let…: Heb. Be not thou hindered from, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Let…: Heb. Be not thou hindered from, etc

verses.text_plain: For I will promote thee unto very great honour, and I will do whatsoever thou sayest unto me: come therefore, I pray thee, curse me this people.
verses.verse_html: 17For I will promote thee unto very great honour, and I will do whatsoever thou sayest unto me: come therefore, I pray thee, curse me this people.

verses.text_plain: And Balaam answered and said unto the servants of Balak, If Balak would give me his house full of silver and gold, I cannot go beyond the word of the Lord my God, to do less or more.
verses.verse_html: 18And Balaam answered and said unto the servants of Balak, If Balak would give me his house full of silver and gold, I cannot go beyond the word of the Lord my God, to do less or more.

verses.text_plain: Now therefore, I pray you, tarry ye also here this night, that I may know what the Lord will say unto me more.
verses.verse_html: 19Now therefore, I pray you, tarry ye also here this night, that I may know what the Lord will say unto me more.

tokens.text: Now therefore, I pray you, tarry

verses.text_plain: And God came unto Balaam at night, and said unto him, If the men come to call thee, rise up, and go with them; but yet the word which I shall say unto thee, that shalt thou do.
verses.verse_html: 20And God came unto Balaam at night, and said unto him, If the men come to call thee, rise up, and go with them; but yet the word which I shall say unto thee, that shalt thou do.

tokens.text: unto thee, that shalt thou do

verses.text_plain: And Balaam rose up in the morning, and saddled his ass, and went with the princes of Moab.
verses.verse_html: 21And Balaam rose up in the morning, and saddled his ass, and went with the princes of Moab.

verses.text_plain: And God’s anger was kindled because he went: and the angel of the Lord stood in the way for an adversary against him. Now he was riding upon his ass, and his two servants were with him.
verses.verse_html: 22And God’s anger was kindled because he went: and the angel of the Lord stood in the way for an adversary against him. Now he was riding upon his ass, and his two servants were with him.

tokens.text: against him. Now he was riding

verses.text_plain: And the ass saw the angel of the Lord standing in the way, and his sword drawn in his hand: and the ass turned aside out of the way, and went into the field: and Balaam smote the ass, to turn her into the way.
verses.verse_html: 23And the ass saw the angel of the Lord standing in the way, and his sword drawn in his hand: and the ass turned aside out of the way, and went into the field: and Balaam smote the ass, to turn her into the way.

verses.text_plain: But the angel of the Lord stood in a path of the vineyards, a wall being on this side, and a wall on that side.
verses.verse_html: 24But the angel of the Lord stood in a path of the vineyards, a wall being on this side, and a wall on that side.

tokens.text: on this side, and a wall

verses.text_plain: And when the ass saw the angel of the Lord, she thrust herself unto the wall, and crushed Balaam’s foot against the wall: and he smote her again.
verses.verse_html: 25And when the ass saw the angel of the Lord, she thrust herself unto the wall, and crushed Balaam’s foot against the wall: and he smote her again.

verses.text_plain: And the angel of the Lord went further, and stood in a narrow place, where was no way to turn either to the right hand or to the left.
verses.verse_html: 26And the angel of the Lord went further, and stood in a narrow place, where was no way to turn either to the right hand or to the left.

verses.text_plain: And when the ass saw the angel of the Lord, she fell down under Balaam: and Balaam’s anger was kindled, and he smote the ass with a staff.
verses.verse_html: 27And when the ass saw the angel of the Lord, she fell down under Balaam: and Balaam’s anger was kindled, and he smote the ass with a staff.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord opened the mouth of the ass, and she said unto Balaam, What have I done unto thee, that thou hast smitten me these three times?
verses.verse_html: 28And the Lord opened the mouth of the ass, and she said unto Balaam, What have I done unto thee, that thou hast smitten me these three times?

tokens.text: unto thee, that thou hast smitten

verses.text_plain: And Balaam said unto the ass, Because thou hast mocked me: I would there were a sword in mine hand, for now would I kill thee.
verses.verse_html: 29And Balaam said unto the ass, Because thou hast mocked me: I would there were a sword in mine hand, for now would I kill thee.

verses.text_plain: And the ass said unto Balaam, Am not I thine ass, upon which thou hast ridden ever since I was thine unto this day? was I ever wont to do so unto thee? And he said, Nay.
verses.verse_html:

verses.text_plain: And the angel of the Lord said unto Balaam, Go with the men: but only the word that I shall speak unto thee, that thou shalt speak. So Balaam went with the princes of Balak.

verses.text_plain: And when Balak heard that Balaam was come, he went out to meet him unto a city of Moab, which is in the border of Arnon, which is in the utmost coast.
verses.verse_html: 36And when Balak heard that Balaam was come, he went out to meet him unto a city of Moab, which is in the border of Arnon, which is in the utmost coast.

verses.text_plain: And Balak said unto Balaam, Did I not earnestly send unto thee to call thee? wherefore camest thou not unto me? am I not able indeed to promote thee to honour?
